  words:
  - beetle
  - beetles
  info: 'Beetles are a part of the largest animal kingdom orders, Coleoptera. The
    life cycle of a typical beetle starts with an egg stage. Once hatched, the larva
    stage begins. The larva will eat and grow eventually turning into a pupa where
    they will be immobile, typically during the winter months. In the spring, the
    adult beetle will emerge and continue the cycle by feeding, mating, and laying
    eggs.


    Source: https://www.webmd.com/a-to-z-guides/beetles-what-to-know '
